HEADWORD: impala
<hw>im*pa"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An antelope
(<spn>Aepyceros melampus</spn>) of Southeastern Africa, the male of
which has ringed lyre-shaped horns, which curve first backward, then
sideways, then upwards. Also called <altname>impalla</altname> and
<altname>pallah</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impalatable</ent>⟦br⟧
